The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, April 01, 2004 				 Rediff signs strategic pact with Yahoo 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, March 31: Rediff.com India and Yahoo! India, arch rivals in the internet portal space, today announced a strategic alliance to jointly promote online shopping and mobile content across both the portals.																								Rediff has an edge over Yahoo in online shopping, while Yahoo has taken a lead in mobile content like ring tones, polyphonic tunes, wallpapers, Java games among others. The two portals hope to gain from this synergy by leveraging on each others value and penetration levels.																								It is the Indian net user who will gain from the combined synergies and strengths of Rediff.com and Yahoo! India, said Neville Taraporewalla, country manager of Yahoo! India. 																								Rediif has 30 million registered users, while Yahoo has 33 million users with 14 million unique users who log on to the Yahoo! India website at least once a week. 																								Ajit Balakrishnan, chairman and CEO of Rediff.com, said, This association collectively leverages our mutual strengths to the benefit of online users across India. 
